    <div class="service-content">
      <p>If you're buying, selling, refinancing, or settling a legal matter involving real property in Las Vegas, you've probably asked yourself: how much is a home appraisal going to cost me? The answer depends on a few factors — but the good news is that for most homeowners, it's less than you might expect.</p>

      <h2>Typical Home Appraisal Costs in Las Vegas</h2>
      <p>In the Las Vegas Valley, residential appraisal fees generally range from $425 to $700 for a standard single-family home. Here's a general breakdown:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Standard single-family home</strong> (under 3,000 sq ft): $425–$550</li>
        <li><strong>Larger homes or complex properties:</strong> $550–$700+</li>
        <li><strong>Condo or townhome:</strong> $425–$500</li>
        <li><strong>Multi-family</strong> (2–4 units): $550–$750</li>
        <li><strong>Rush/expedited service:</strong> add $75–$150</li>
      </ul>

      <p>Factors that can increase the fee include unusual property features, hard-to-find comparable sales, large lot sizes, rural locations (such as Pahrump), or tight turnaround requirements.</p>

      <h2>What Does the Fee Include?</h2>
      <p>A certified appraisal fee covers the appraiser's time to inspect the property, research comparable sales, analyze market trends, and prepare a complete written report. The report typically includes a full property description, photos, a market analysis, and the appraiser's certified opinion of value.</p>

      <h2>Is a Cheap Appraisal Worth It?</h2>
      <p>It can be tempting to shop for the lowest price — but when it comes to appraisals, quality matters. A poorly supported appraisal can be rejected by lenders, challenged in court, or simply get the value wrong. For a legal matter like a divorce or estate, an inaccurate appraisal can cost far more than the fee savings.</p>

      <p>At Las Vegas Appraisal Co., every report passes a 6-point quality control review before delivery. Our appraisers have 40+ years of local market experience and are Nevada State Certified and FHA-approved.</p>

